<p>
"Just as in the case of electricity the modern theory is that the power leaves the dynamo and completes the circle back to the dynamo, so with hate and love; they must come back to the source. Therefore do not hate anybody, because that hatred which comes out from you, must, in the long run, come back to you. If you love, that love will come back to you, completing the circle. It is as certain as can be, that every bit of hatred that goes out of the heart of a man comes back to him in full force, nothing can stop it; similarly every impulse of love comes back to him."<br><br>
- Swami Vivekananda, "Patanjali's Yoga Aphorisms: Introduction" (Beginning raja yoga class, Jan 11, 1896, New York), Raja Yoga, Complete Works: Vol 1
</p>
